     Removal      : Delete Virusfile.

     Comments     : The  BGS9-Virus  was the first filevirus which useses
                    another  way  to infect disks. If you`re starting the
                    virus  it  changes the KICK-Vectors to stay resident.
                    The  virus  is  located  in the CHIP-Memory which was
                    allocated  before.  After  the next  reset  the virus
                    patches  the  OpenWin()-Vector form the intuition.lib
                    This patch will be used for the infection.

                    Imagine  you`re  inserting an clean unprotected disk:

                    1) The  virus  forbids ALL system-requesters to avoid
                       messages like "Disk is Write-Protected"....

                    2) Then  the  virus checks for the invisible filename
                       "devs:$a0a0202020a0202020a0". If existing the disk
                       was already infected.

                    3) Now  the  virus checks for the first executed file
                       in  the  startup-sequence. This file will be moved
                       as  "$a0a0202020a0202020a0" in the devs-directory.

                    4) After  that  the  virus  creates the own virusfile
                       with  the  name of the file which was moved in the
                       devs-directory before.

                    You   see the virus doesn`t modifies the startup-seq.
                    with  any  virusfilename, so for many users the virus
                    was  simply "invisible". But now you will say "What`s
                    about  the  Original  file in Devs?". Yeah! this file
                    will  be executed, too (on the next boot-up). You can
                    easyly   remove  this virus  by recopying the renamed
                    invisible  file  in devs  to  the  original file (The
                    first file in Startup-Sequence!). 

                    Depending of a value (don`t know exactly what value.)
                    the  virus  gives  out  a GFX-Message telling you the
                    following:


                          A COMPUTER VIRUS IS A DISEASE
                          TERRORISM IS A TRANSGRESSION
